<subSubSection id="C31A6561FFE8FF80FE97F3FCF7570615" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FE97F3FCFB1C0C9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80FE97F3FCFE730C7F" bold="true" box="[257,420,3126,3160]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Diagnosis</emphasis>
based on living and preserved aquarium-bred specimens, two living wild specimens of unknown origin and a large number of wild preserved specimens from Colombia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FA96FA2EF7570615" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
New information is given in italics. For some details distinguishing 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80FA06F9D3F99D0611" authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[1424,1610,1561,1590]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.bestMatchDistance="3210" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80FA06F9D3F99D0611" box="[1424,1610,1561,1590]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">P. ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F93AF9D3F874061D" box="[1708,1955,1561,1594]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apístogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F93AF9D3F874061D" bold="true" box="[1708,1955,1561,1594]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Apístogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see Table I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31A6561FFE8FF80FAB1F987FA430A0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FAB1F987F7CD06F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
Small neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F9CAF987F922064E" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1835" box="[1628,1781,1613,1641]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Cichlidae</taxonomicName>
with a small lobe on the ﬁrst epibranchial. 3-4 small rakers along the margin of the lobe, 6 along the lateral rim of the ﬁrst ceratobranchial.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FAB4F927F9EE0763" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
A 
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80FAC7F926F9EE0763" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">single supraneural. N0 rakers along the edges 0f the lower pharyngeals.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FABEF89CF7B30780" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">2 lateral lines on each side, the terminal scale of the upper (anterior) at 1 -1 % scales distance from the dorsal ﬁn.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FAB2F808F987083F" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80FAB2F808F987083F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">First dorsal spine inserted behind vertical line from hind margin of gill-cover.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FAB4F7E1FA4D08A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80FAB4F7E1FA4D08A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Body scales ctenoid, occasionally cycloid elements preventrally.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FABFF75FF8550896" box="[1321,1922,2197,2232]" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Fins naked, except proximal caudal.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FABFF701FAA9093C" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
Preoperculum naked, 
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F935F706FAA3093C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">its vertical hind margin smooth or serrate</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FABCF6FEF8C009A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Mouth small, subinferior. Lacrimal bone narrow, its depth less than å the diameter of orbit.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FABDF655FA430A0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Secondary sex differences slight. Monogamous, openbreeder on horizontal surfaces or in pits, brood-care biparental.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31A6561FFE8FF80FABAF5F7F8480AB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FABAF5F7F8480AB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
Type-species
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F99FF5F7F86A0A7C" box="[1545,1981,2621,2656]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F9B3F5F4FA9A0AA9" authority="Myers &amp; Harry, 1948" authorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" authorityYear="1948" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">Apistogramma ramirezi Myers &amp; Harry, 1948</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. The genus is currently monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A98240BCB5D066AF4EBA986B11DC32CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C5B94A8E302966422DA1B100A54176DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis id="455275F82134D5CD5501DAE82C71175B" bold="true" box="[1315,1731,2743,2774]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
Etymology. 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80FA75F57DF9140AF1" authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="SVEN O. KULLANDER" authorityYear="1977" box="[1507,1731,2743,2774]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Papiliochromis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is derived from a combination of two generic names, 
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F9BCF515F9440AD9" bold="true" box="[1578,1683,2783,2814]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F9BCF515F9440AD9" box="[1578,1683,2783,2814]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papílio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Papílio</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F93AF515F8880AD9" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1708,1887,2783,2814]" class="Insecta" family="Malvaceae" genus="Lepidoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
) and 
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F825F52AF7F90ADF" bold="true" box="[1971,2094,2784,2808]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F825F52AF7F90ADF" box="[1971,2094,2784,2808]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromís" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Chromís</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(formerly the generic name of many cichlids, now a pomacentrid genus). The meaning would be “Butterﬂy Cichlid” in allusion to the international popular name. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DF55CB8D74884B1E0367B86225EAA399" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="254" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF80FA95F427FA0E0C37" box="[1283,1497,3053,3088]" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
<heading id="D0F78186FFE8FF80FA95F427FA0E0C37" bold="true" box="[1283,1497,3053,3088]" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" reason="2">Relationships</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36EAFFE8FF81FA93F3F8FE230523" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="254" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
There are no indications suggesting that P. 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F844F3FDF78C0C72" authorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" authorityYear="1948" box="[2002,2139,3127,3157]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F844F3FDF78C0C72" bold="true" box="[2002,2139,3127,3157]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is particularly closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE8FF80F90DF3A6F8450CAA" authorityName="Reproductive behaviour Monogamous, open-breeder, eggs laid on horizontal surfaces or in pits, brood-care biparental Polygynous, concealment breeder, eggs laid on vertical or rooﬁng surfaces, maternal brood-care" authorityYear="1913" box="[1691,1938,3180,3213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F90DF3A6F8450CAA" bold="true" box="[1691,1938,3180,3213]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Apistogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. What suggested the original classiﬁcation was probably in the ﬁrst place the 
<heading id="D0F78186FFE8FF80F863F33DF7240D2B" bold="true" box="[2037,2291,3319,3346]" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F863F33DF7AF0D36" bold="true" box="[2037,2168,3319,3345]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Z oologica</emphasis>
S 
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE8FF80F702F332F7240D2B" bold="true" box="[2196,2291,3319,3346]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">cripta 6</emphasis>
</heading>
For 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE9FF81FF29FEE9FE4F0167" authorityName="Reproductive behaviour Monogamous, open-breeder, eggs laid on horizontal surfaces or in pits, brood-care biparental Polygynous, concealment breeder, eggs laid on vertical or rooﬁng surfaces, maternal brood-care" authorityYear="1913" box="[191,408,291,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE9FF81FF29FEE9FE4F0167" box="[191,408,291,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Apistogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, morphological data is based on about 40 spp., behaviour on about 10 spp. New information is in italics. small size in combination with the presence of an epibranchial lobe, but in 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D69FFE9FF81FED9FBB5FDDD04BB" box="[335,522,1151,1180]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papílio" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramírezi">
<emphasis id="B974EAF8FFE9FF81FED9FBB5FDDD04BB" box="[335,522,1151,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramírezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lobe is much smaller, as already pointed out by Myers &amp; Harry (1948), and the small size is probably coincidental.
</paragraph>
